<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Scottish_Gaelic&amp;action=edit&amp;section=25" title="Edit section: Scottish Gaelic for beginners">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Scottish Gaelic for beginners</span></h3>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.bbc.co.uk/scotland/alba/foghlam/airsplaoid/index.shtml" class="external text" title="http://www.bbc.co.uk/scotland/alba/foghlam/airsplaoid/index.shtml" rel="nofollow">Air Splaoid!</a> Discover Gaelic with Dwelly, a free online Gaelic language course.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.bbc.co.uk/scotland/alba/foghlam/learngaelic/index.shtml" class="external text" title="http://www.bbc.co.uk/scotland/alba/foghlam/learngaelic/index.shtml" rel="nofollow">BBC Learn Gaelic</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.cli.org.uk" class="external text" title="http://www.cli.org.uk" rel="nofollow">CLI Gàidhlig</a> Gaelic supporters and learners organisation that produces the bilingual magazine <i>Cothrom</i></li>
<li><a href="http://www.elacademy.co.uk/gaelic-courses.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.elacademy.co.uk/gaelic-courses.htm" rel="nofollow">ELAcademy</a> Gaelic language courses in Edinburgh.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.ambaile.org" class="external text" title="http://www.ambaile.org" rel="nofollow">AmBaile.org - Home of Highland Gaelic culture</a> Online games for Scottish Gaelic learners</li>
<li><a href="http://www.akerbeltz.org" class="external text" title="http://www.akerbeltz.org" rel="nofollow">Akerbeltz - A’ Ghobhar Dhubh</a> Gaelic Resources (grammar, pronunciation, rhymes, names ...)</li>
<li><a href="http://www.omniglot.com/writing/gaelic.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.omniglot.com/writing/gaelic.htm" rel="nofollow">Scottish Gaelic</a> at Omniglot</li>
<li><a href="http://www.smo.uhi.ac.uk/gaidhlig/ionnsachadh/" class="external text" title="http://www.smo.uhi.ac.uk/gaidhlig/ionnsachadh/" rel="nofollow">Learners' material online</a></li>
<li><a href="http://topsearchesnews.com/gaelic.asp" class="external text" title="http://topsearchesnews.com/gaelic.asp" rel="nofollow">BBC Can Seo - Gaelic for Beginners</a> book and videos from the 1970s</li>
